<head>Introduction For <person>Frank Hankins</person></head>
<p>One of the most encouraging aspects of this movement is to witness the rise of a new
generation of educators and leaders of opinion.  <add>(</add> College professors used to be
notorious for their ignorance concerning life or anything outside their own specialty.  They were
hard&hyphen;shelled reactionaries concerning the vital problems of humanity.<add>)</add> It is my
honor now to introduce a fine representative of the new educator, a man who is courag<del>ing</del><add>eous</add>  in his outspoken attitude concerning the fundamental ethical  <add>moral</add>  necessity for education in Birth Control&hyphen;&hyphen;Dr. Frank Hankins</p>
</docBody>
